al_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 3006, \"end\": 3013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999997880877, \"rank\": 2.1192638836488663e-10, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3040, \"end\": 3046, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999999980294888, \"rank\": 1.9248956727267255e-08, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a four-timeNBAchampion\", \"from\": 2775, \"to\": 2797}, {\"ngram\": \"the league's all-time leading scorer\", \"from\": 2802, \"to\": 2838}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2907, \"to\": 2919}, {\"ngram\": \"the fourth time\", \"from\": 2924, \"to\": 2939}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 2954, \"to\": 2958}, {\"ngram\": \"U.S. teams\", \"from\": 2962, \"to\": 2972}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 2982, \"to\": 2988}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 3026, \"to\": 3030}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He walked in the opening ceremony at each of his three previous Olympics.\", \"from\": 3056, \"to\": 3129, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 3069, \"to\": 3089}, {\"ngram\": \"his three previous Olympics\", \"from\": 3101, \"to\": 3128}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This time, he will float.\", \"from\": 3131, \"to\": 3156, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This will be an opening ceremony like none other in Olympic history: Thousands of athletes will be part of a flotilla sailing along the River Seine at sunset toward the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 3158, \"to\": 3340, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3294, \"end\": 3305, \"titl